In-Reply-To: nils mccarthy's message of Tue, 16 Nov 1993 15:37:37 -0700 &lt;9311162237.AA18919@mcmuse.mc.maricopa.edu&gt;


&gt; i always thought clearish variables should work in the following way:
&gt;
&gt; if a variable had the same value as the one on its parent, it would be
&gt; considered clear, and not stored in the database.

	What if my variable has the same value as the one on the parent
because I *want* it to be that value, and they just happen to be the
same value?  I think the Lambda approach is most reasonable;  set up 
some sort of value representing "the empty set" and refer to the parent's
variable in that case.

Steven J. Owens
uso01@unidata.com
